# Native-Windows ops box: Lisp/ASDF sources MUST check out as LF.
#
# SBCL reads source files verbatim; the CL FORMAT "~<newline>" line-fold
# directive (used as `~%~` at end of line) becomes `~\r` under CRLF and
# raises "error in FORMAT: Unknown directive (character: Return)", aborting
# compilation (see src/lisp/school/advisors.lisp). CRLF also injects stray
# carriage returns into multi-line string literals that feed S-expr/ZMQ
# payloads and Discord/log output. Force LF regardless of core.autocrlf.
*.lisp text eol=lf
*.asd  text eol=lf
